## CLI Search Implementation Analysis

I've thoroughly explored the HQ project's CLI (harness) and identified the complete search command structure and patterns. Here's what I found:

### 1. **Command Structure (clap Derive Macros)**

**File:** `/Users/anotonio.silva/antonio/HQ/src-tauri/src/bin/harness.rs`

#### Top-level CLI struct:
```rust
#[derive(Parser)]
#[command(name = "harness")]
#[command(author, version, about = "Harness CLI - Database utility for AI agents")]
#[command(propagate_version = true)]
struct Cli {
    /// Output format
    #[arg(long, value_enum, global = true, default_value = "text")]
    format: OutputFormat,

    /// Project directory (defaults to current directory)
    #[arg(short = 'C', long, global = true)]
    dir: Option<PathBuf>,

    #[command(subcommand)]
    command: Commands,
}
```

#### OutputFormat enum (global flag across all commands):
```rust
#[derive(Copy, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, ValueEnum)]
enum OutputFormat {
    Text,      // Human-readable (default)
    Json,      // Programmatic use
    Quiet,     // IDs only (one per line)
}
```

### 2. **Search Commands Structure**

#### TaskCommands::Search (lines 140-148):
```rust
#[derive(Subcommand)]
enum TaskCommands {
    /// Search tasks using full-text search
    Search {
        /// Search query
        query: String,

        /// Maximum number of results
        #[arg(short, long, default_value = "20")]
        limit: usize,
    },
    // ... other task commands
}
```

#### ProgressCommands::Search (lines 340-348):
```rust
#[derive(Subcommand)]
enum ProgressCommands {
    /// Search progress using full-text search
    Search {
